# Terraform standards — {{WORKSPACE_NAME}}

> **Purpose**: The authoritative engineering-conventions document for Terraform / HCL repos in this workspace. Module layout, naming, state management, resource patterns — **how we write Terraform here**, not architecture (that's `platform.md`).
> **Last Updated**: {{DATE}}
> **Bootstrapped by**: PipeCrew `/discover` — Phase B2.5.

Terraform repos manage infrastructure-as-code. The implementer never runs `terraform apply` — only `terraform fmt` + `terraform validate` + `terraform plan` (the plan output is the artifact for human review). This document captures the workspace's conventions for the parts the implementer DOES author.

**Stable section anchors (§1–§9) are cited by number from implementer and reviewer agents.** Do not renumber existing sections; you may add §10+.

